Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Cut the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into thin 1cm slices, then cut into thin 1cm
wide fries (no need to peel).

Pop the fries onto a #large baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, sprinkle over half
the @Central American Style Spice Mix{1%sachet}, season with @salt{} and
@ground black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

== Pickled Onion ==

Meanwhile, halve the @lime{1}. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the
flesh out onto a #cutting board{} and cut into 1cm chunks. Quarter the
@baby plum tomatoes{125%g}.

In a #small bowl{}, add the red onion, the juice from half the lime, the
@sugar{1%tsp} and a pinch of salt. Mix together and set aside.

== Avocado Salsa ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the avocado, tomatoes, a drizzle of @olive oil{}
and a squeeze of lime. Season with salt and pepper, then set aside.

>= 2/3 of the avocado salsa can be made ahead of time and refrigerated.

== Tofu Tacos ==

Drain the @firm tofu{280%g} and cut into slices (3 per person), then cut each
slice in half again. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{} and sprinkle over the
remaining Central American style spice mix, pressing it in so it sticks. Season
with salt and pepper.

Crack the @egg{1} into another medium bowl and whisk.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{50%g} into another medium bowl and season with the
@salt{1/4%tsp} and pepper.

Dip the tofu into the egg, then the breadcrumbs, ensuring it's completely
coated. Shake off the excess and transfer to a clean #plate{}.

Pop a #large frying pan{} on high heat and add enough oil to completely coat
the bottom of the pan.

> You want the oil to be hot so the tofu fries properly - heat for 2-3 mins before
> you add the tofu.

Once the oil is hot, carefully lay the tofu into the pan, reduce the heat to
medium-high and fry until golden-brown, ~{4-6%minutes} each side. Adjust the
heat if necessary.

> Fry in batches if needed, adding more oil to the pan if it's looking dry.

Transfer the tofu to a plate lined with kitchen paper.

== Assembly ==

While the tofu fries, trim the @iceberg lettuce{1}, halve lengthways, then thinly
slice.

In a small bowl, combine the @chipotle paste{20%g} (use less if you'd prefer
things milder) and @soured cream{150%g}.

When the wedges have a few mins left, pop the @plain taco tortillas{6} onto a
baking tray and into the oven to warm through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

When everything's ready, transfer the tortillas to your plates. Spread over the
chipotle soured cream, then top with the lettuce.

Top with the crispy tofu and pickled onion - as much as you'd like.

Serve your tacos with the avocado salsa and spiced chips alongside.

> Tacos are best enjoyed eaten by hand - get stuck in!